section.section:
Each insurer providing professional liability insurance to a health care provider in the State shall submit to the Commissioner information on:
the nature and cost of reinsurance;
the claims experience, by category, of health care providers;
the amount of claim settlements and claim awards;
the amount of reserves for claims incurred and incurred but unreported claims;
the number of structured settlements used in payment of claims; and
any other information relating to health care malpractice claims prescribed by the Commissioner in regulation.

text.section:
In addition to the information required under subsection (a) of this section, for each claim filed with the Director of the Health Care Alternative Dispute Resolution Office under § 3-2A-04 of the Courts Article, each insurer providing professional liability insurance to a health care provider in the State shall submit to the Commissioner the following information:
name of insurer;
name of insurer group;
claim file identification;
name of person completing form;
telephone number (area code); and
date form completed;
date of injury;
date injury reported to insurer; and
date claim closed;
age and gender of insured person at time of injury;
type of injury;
description of injury; and
if the claim is against a health care provider covered under a policy issued or delivered by the insurer completing this form, the name of the health facility where the injury occurred;
type of medical professional liability policy;
if known, whether the patient was:
physician ISO classification, or equivalent classification;
health care provider name and license number; and
policy limits for:
if known, the facility, office, or county where injury occurred; and
the case number and the name and location of the court where the suit was filed and the case was tried;
whether settlement was reached or award was made at one of the following stages:
if settlement was reached or award was made by court verdict, whether the result was:
if there was no final judgment or settlement, the date and reason for the final disposition; and
if the case did go to trial, whether the case was tried by a jury;
with respect to the total amount paid to the claimant:
the amount paid by the insurer;
the amount paid by the insured due to retention or deductible;
if known, the amount paid by an excess carrier;
if known, the amount paid by the insured due to settlement or award in excess of policy limits;
if known, the amount paid by other defendants or contributors; and
the total amount of settlement or award;
a summary of the occurrence from which the claim or action arose, including:
a description of the misdiagnosis or alleged misdiagnosis made, if any, of the patient's actual condition;
a description of the procedure giving rise to the claim; and
a description of the principal injury giving rise to the claim;
whether a structured settlement or periodic payment was used in closing this claim; and
if a structured settlement or periodic payment was used:
if a neutral expert witness is employed under § 3-2A-09(d)(2) of the Courts Article, the findings of a neutral expert witness as to a plaintiff's future medical expenses or future loss of earnings;
if the case was tried to verdict, the amount of noneconomic damages; and
the total allocated loss adjustment expense by fees and expenses paid to defense counsel; and
the total allocated loss adjustment expense.
